v:4 c:$ m:T04-stub-time-travel-slider role:dev x:vue3/typescript
gate: LOCKED

task: Replace TimeTravelSlider.vue with a self-contained audio time-scrub stub

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
out:
  - daww3/experiments/jam-sandbox/src/components/ui/TimeTravelSlider.vue

context: |
  Current file imports useTimeTravel, useTimeline, useReplay (from
  composables/core/*) and vue-router — none of these exist in jam-sandbox.
  The component will fail to compile as-is.

  In jam-sandbox context "time travel" maps to audio playback scrubbing:
  scrub a position value (0..1 or 0..durationMs) passed in via props/model.
  No Supabase event history needed.

new-api:
  props:
    min: number (default 0)
    max: number (default 100)
    disabled?: boolean
  modelValue: number (v-model)
  emits: update:modelValue

steps:
  1. Rewrite TimeTravelSlider.vue from scratch.
  2. Props: min (0), max (100), modelValue (number), disabled (false).
  3. Emit update:modelValue on input change.
  4. Template: single <input type="range"> with Tailwind styling matching the
     existing slider in the taskboard version (accent-indigo-500, etc.).
  5. No router, no composables, no supabase imports.

done:
  - Component compiles without TS errors in jam-sandbox
  - Renders a styled range input that emits value changes
  - v-model works: <TimeTravelSlider v-model="pos" :min="0" :max="duration" />
